HEADWORD: vitamin A2
<hw>vitamin A2</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>dehydroretinol
(<chform>C20H28O</chform>), one of the substances also called
<altname>vitamin A</altname>. It has about 40% of the bioactivity of
vitamin A1.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> dehydroretinol.</syn>⟦br⟧
